The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the areas of algorithms and machine learning. The use of a knapsack constraint is also a common topic in optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents an algorithm with an improved approximation ratio, which suggests that it could be relevant to the areas of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization and game theory concepts, which could make it relevant to the categories of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
